20
00:01:32,421 --> 00:01:38,385
So Sunless Skies is a narrative roguelike RPG. You play the captain of a space train

21
00:01:39,026 --> 00:01:41,467
in a world where the Victorian empire goes to space,

22
00:01:42,248 --> 00:01:44,990
finds it riddled with cosmic horror and then makes it worse.

23
00:01:47,337 --> 00:01:53,999
And the game combines two modes of play, a real-time exploration mode where you have direct

24
00:01:54,039 --> 00:01:59,781
control over your space train and you fly around and explore and fight enemies and gather resources.

25
00:02:00,541 --> 00:02:07,943
And then when you interact with a discovery or dock at a port, we switch to an elaborate

26
00:02:08,063 --> 00:02:12,684
interactive fiction mode where the player gets to explore the location in a text-based interface.

27
00:02:15,676 --> 00:02:18,578
Sunless Skies was well received, both commercially and critically.

28
00:02:19,078 --> 00:02:21,380
Here are excerpts from some of its reviews,

29
00:02:22,020 --> 00:02:23,661
including the poignant and haunting,

