00:02:53,942 --> 00:02:58,705
Sea. So we knew we wanted a less centralized creative direction.

38
00:02:59,573 --> 00:03:02,454
more opportunities for team members to contribute ideas to the game,

39
00:03:03,314 --> 00:03:06,876
and for departments to feel confident in working more independently.

40
00:03:09,417 --> 00:03:14,439
And the scale of a narrative task in front of us was pretty daunting.

41
00:03:17,023 --> 00:03:23,350
It took place in a setting that by then was eight years old and had millions of words dedicated to

42
00:03:23,410 --> 00:03:33,239
it. The Fallen London Universe lore bible is about 137 pages long and they are 137 pages of complicated

43
00:03:33,279 --> 00:03:39,105
and dense lore and we didn't want that to put players off. We wanted Skies to be a good entry

44
00:03:39,145 --> 00:03:40,026
point into the universe.

45
00:03:42,605 --> 00:03:45,487
It was also set in a baroque and unfamiliar environment.

46
00:03:45,988 --> 00:03:48,870
So Sunless Skies is set in space, but not as we know it.

47
00:03:49,651 --> 00:03:52,573
It has winds and sentient malevolent suns

48
00:03:52,733 --> 00:03:54,054
and starlight that drives you mad.

49
00:03:55,255 --> 00:03:58,097
So players and ourselves on the team

50
00:03:58,477 --> 00:04:00,939
couldn't rely on common science fictional assumptions

51
00:04:01,539 --> 00:04:02,320
to make sense of it.

52
00:04:04,761 --> 00:04:07,664
It was also, we knew, going to be really big.

53
00:04:09,119 --> 00:04:16,308
Specifically, it ended up being 800,000 words big, which is 1.6 women pieces, or the first

54
00:04:16,348 --> 00:04:22,215
two and a half Game of Thrones books, or 19 seconds of Twitter, which is a nightmare we

